</node>
<node id="&quot;EXTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MUSCLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"External Intercostal Muscles are a pair of muscles that start from ribs one through eleven and connect at a slight angle downward to ribs two through twelve, aiding in inhalation.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 116}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MUSCLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Internal Intercostal Muscles are a pair of muscles that start from ribs two through twelve and connect upward to ribs one through eleven, aiding in exhalation.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INHALATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inhalation is the process of drawing air into the lungs, facilitated by the contraction of the diaphragm and external intercostal muscles.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Inhalation is the process of drawing air into the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 116}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXHALATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Exhalation is the process of expelling air from the lungs, facilitated by the relaxation of the diaphragm and the contraction of the internal intercostal muscles.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Exhalation is the process of expelling air from the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THORAX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The thorax is the chest cavity that houses the heart and lungs, and its movement is crucial for breathing.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Thorax is the upper part of the trunk of the body, protecting vital organs such as the heart and lungs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thorax refers to the upper part of the trunk of the body, containing the heart and lungs, and is covered by the rib cage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RIBS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ribs are bones that form the framework of the thoracic cage, connecting to muscles that aid in breathing.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LUNGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lungs are organs that facilitate the exchange of oxygen and carbon dioxide during respiration."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lungs are the primary organs responsible for gas exchange, expanding and contracting during inhalation and exhalation.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHONATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Phonation is the production of sound by the vocal folds, which requires pressure generated by the lungs.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Folds are the primary components that produce sound in the vocal mechanism."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal folds are the structures in the larynx that vibrate to produce sound during phonation.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19f493d7c41902144de9bdc890a5c45a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNAL INTERCOSTALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Internal Intercostals are a group of muscles that start from ribs two through twelve and connect upward to ribs one through eleven, contracting to induce exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RECTUS ABDOMINIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rectus Abdominis is a pair of muscles running from the pubic bone to the sternum, divided into four separate portions called bellies, which can result in a 'ripped' or 'six-pack' appearance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 73}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXTERNAL OBLIQUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"External Oblique is a large muscle of the abdomen that runs at a downward angle from the sides of the rectus, covering the lower portion of the thorax, and extending to the spine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNAL OBLIQUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Internal Oblique is a muscle layer located below the external obliques, oriented at an angle that crisscrosses the external muscles, starting at the bottom of the thorax."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRANSVERSE ABDOMINIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Transverse Abdominis is the deepest muscle layer in the abdomen, providing support and stability to the abdominal region."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transverse Abdominis is the deepest muscle layer in the abdominal region, with fibers running horizontally and encasing the abdominal area."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Spine is the series of vertebrae that runs along the back and supports the upper body."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PUBIC BONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pubic Bone is a part of the pelvis located at the front of the hip bones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 73}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STERNUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sternum is the flat bone in the center of the chest, to which the ribs are attached."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8f2f286333556f509cc2f70199e6ad4</data>
</node>
