</node>
<node id="&quot;OBLIQUES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Obliques refer to a group of muscles located in the abdomen, oriented at an angle and slightly smaller than other abdominal muscles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXPIRATORY MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Expiratory muscles are large and capable of producing significant pulmonary pressure, often overpowering the larynx in healthy adults."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 115}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BICEPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Biceps are flexor muscles that work in opposition to extensor muscles like the triceps, demonstrating muscular antagonism."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 114}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRICEPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Triceps are extensor muscles that work in opposition to flexor muscles like the biceps, demonstrating muscular antagonism."&lt;SEP&gt;"triceps refers to extensors, which are muscles responsible for straightening the arm at the elbow."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 72}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXTERNAL INTERCOSTALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"External Intercostals are muscles located between the ribs and assist in the breathing process, particularly during exhalation for controlling respiratory pressure."&lt;SEP&gt;"external intercostals are muscles located between the ribs that assist in the expansion of the chest during inhalation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 114}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THORACIC MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thoracic muscles include the obliques and transverse abdominis, which are part of the abdominal muscle layers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARYNX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larynx is the voice box, which can be overpowered by the expiratory muscles during exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 115}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PULMONARY PRESSURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pulmonary pressure is the pressure exerted by the lungs during respiration, which can be controlled by expiratory muscles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 115}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BREATH SUPPORT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Breath support is a technique used by singers to control and moderate airflow and breath pressure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSCULAR ANTAGONISM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Muscular antagonism is the principle where muscles work in opposing directions to increase stability or motor control."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 75}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 114}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESPIRATORY PRESSURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Respiratory Pressure refers to the force generated by the diaphragm and intercostal muscles during breathing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Respiratory pressure is the force generated by the respiratory muscles during inhalation and exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 54}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSPIRATORY MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inspiratory muscles include the diaphragm and external intercostals, which are responsible for drawing air into the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 54}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AIRFLOW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Airflow refers to the movement of air in and out of the lungs during respiration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 54}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ICEPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"iceps refers to flexors, which are muscles responsible for bending the arm at the elbow."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 72}]</data>
