  <data key="d1">"A feeder is used to provide food to the bees, typically placed in the hive to supply sugar water or other nutrients."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeder is a component used in beekeeping to provide food to the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeder is a container used to provide food to bees, typically a 1-gallon glass jar with a tight-fitting lid and perforated holes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeder is a device used to provide syrup to bees, aiding in their nutrition and management."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeder is a device used to provide syrup to the bees, aiding in feeding and maintaining the colony during times of scarcity."</data>
