<node id="&quot;BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bees are a group of insects working together to maintain the hive and perform various tasks such as pollination and honey production."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are described as arriving in remarkable condition despite harsh conditions, indicating their resilience and health."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are insects that are kept in hives and require feeding to maintain their health and productivity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are insects that collect and store pollen, adding enzymes to preserve and enhance its value, and are responsible for wax secretion dependent on sugar consumption."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are insects that produce honey and pollinate flowers, playing a crucial role in agriculture and ecosystems."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are insects that work together in a hive to produce honey and maintain the colony, playing a crucial role in the survival and growth of the bee population."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are social insects living in colonies, with a structured hierarchy including workers, drones, and a queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are social insects that form a colony and work together to maintain the hive, produce honey, and pollinate plants."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are social insects that work together in a hive, performing various tasks such as foraging and maintaining the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the insects managed in the hive and are the primary focus of the beekeeping process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the insects responsible for collecting pollen and communicating within the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary members of the new colony, numbering approximately 10,000 in a package."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary recipients of the syrup from the feeder and can be affected by leaks and other issues."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary subjects of care and installation, consisting of both young bees and nurse bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the workers within the hive, performing various tasks such as pollination and honey production."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees refer to the family Apidae, including honey bees, bumblebees, and orchid bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-517c563bb28c6e8e2284f65f24dada91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b76cb7a97a0a93c1fb8f78f65cc66f8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4b59df57b1e25c48127580d5e99112f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6e4f97eb5bc0f6ae5d51fafc8480e48&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cf50994b52751855b1afce08fc2fcd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f9b065adde9eed358d0bfd3a26e87da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19f493d7c41902144de9bdc890a5c45a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
</node>
