<node id="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A package in this context likely refers to a screened box containing bees, workers, drones, a queen, and syrup, used in beekeeping."&lt;SEP&gt;"A package is a unit of bees used to start a new colony, containing approximately 10,000 bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"A package is an event where bees are collected and prepared for relocation, typically involving the separation of bees from their parent colony and the introduction of a new queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package is a temporary housing for bees during transportation or relocation, designed to protect and contain the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package is a unit containing a new queen bee and attendant bees, used to introduce a new queen to a hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package refers to a group of young bees and nurse bees enclosed in a cage, intended for installation in a hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package refers to the structure containing bees that needs to be installed in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A beekeeper is someone who collects pollen from the hive entrance and cleans, dries, and stores it for later use."&lt;SEP&gt;"A beekeeper is someone who collects pollen from the hive entrance and processes it for storage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeper is a person who manages and cares for bee colonies, including feeding them."&lt;SEP&gt;"The beekeeper is responsible for managing the new colony and providing assistance when needed."&lt;SEP&gt;"The beekeeper is responsible for monitoring the progress of the package and providing necessary assistance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-517c563bb28c6e8e2284f65f24dada91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A queen cage is a container used to transport a queen bee, often separate from a package of bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage is a container within the package that holds the queen bee."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage is a device used to confine the queen bee during transportation and introduction into a new hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage is a device used to house a queen bee during the process of introducing her to a new colony, ensuring she cannot escape until the bees accept her."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NUC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A nuc is a nucleus colony, a small colony used to start a new larger colony, which includes frames with brood and bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inner cover is a protective layer placed between the top bars and the outer cover of the hive, providing insulation and protection."&lt;SEP&gt;"Inner cover is a protective layer placed between the top bars of the frames and the outer cover of the hive, providing insulation and protection."&lt;SEP&gt;"The inner cover is a protective layer placed between the top of the hive and the outer cover to prevent moisture from entering the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece</data>
</node>
