  <data key="d2">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Frames are structures within the hive that hold comb and honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Frames are structures within the hive used to hold comb and honey, essential for the organization and storage of bee products."&lt;SEP&gt;"Frames are the individual sections of a hive that hold the comb and are removable for inspection and management."&lt;SEP&gt;"Frames are the individual sections within the hive where comb is built, holding the queen cage in place."&lt;SEP&gt;"Frames are used to organize the brood and bees within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
</node>
