<node id="&quot;QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen is a female bee, specifically the new queen introduced into the package to lead the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen is the female bee that lays eggs and is the central figure in the bee colony, responsible for maintaining the population and genetic diversity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen refers to the female bee that lays eggs and is the central figure in the bee colony, responsible for maintaining the genetic continuity of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"The queen bee is the reproductive female of the colony, responsible for laying eggs and maintaining the genetic diversity of the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"The queen is a crucial member of the colony, responsible for laying eggs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A hive is the structure where the bees live and build their comb."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is a location where the Supporting Lenders are patrolling."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the home of the bees, where they live, work, and store resources."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the permanent home for the bees, where they will be installed after receiving proper care."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees are placed, often early in the season when there is little forage available."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees live and store syrup, and can be affected by leaks from the feeder."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees live and work, consisting of multiple frames containing honeycomb cells for storing honey and raising brood."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees live, store food, and raise their young, serving as their home and workplace."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees live, store food, and raise their young."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees live, work, and store honey, characterized by its complex architecture and social organization."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive refers to a structured environment where bees are kept and managed for beekeeping purposes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive refers to the structure where bees live and produce honey, typically consisting of multiple frames with wax comb."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive refers to the structure where bees live and store pollen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive refers to the structure where bees live and work, managed by beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-517c563bb28c6e8e2284f65f24dada91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b76cb7a97a0a93c1fb8f78f65cc66f8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4b59df57b1e25c48127580d5e99112f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cf50994b52751855b1afce08fc2fcd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c92a9c5dc2f4c6438fabee7122c013&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
