<node id="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollen is a fine powder produced by plants that bees collect for food and to help in plant reproduction."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is a natural substance produced by plants and collected by bees, essential for bee nutrition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is a protein-rich substance that can be collected and stored by beekeepers for feeding bees during times of need."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is a substance collected and stored by bees, containing enzymes and other substances that help preserve and enhance its value, and is a source of vitamins, minerals, and fats."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is the fine powder collected by worker bees from flowers, used as a protein source for the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is the fine powder produced by plants that is collected by bees to provide protein and other nutrients."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-517c563bb28c6e8e2284f65f24dada91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VITAMINS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vitamins are essential for the growth and development of any living organism, and are found in high quantities in pollen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MINERALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Minerals are collected by bees as part of nectar, pollen, and water, necessary for various functions at specific ages, and can be detrimental if deficient or present in excess."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FATS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fats are a component of pollen, used for daily needs, and stored in fat bodies within the bee's body cavity, which vary with the season and the age of the bee."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FAT BODIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fat Bodies are storage sites for food reserves within the body cavity of honey bees, primarily developed from sugar rather than pollen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wax is secreted by bees, dependent on sugar consumption rather than pollen consumption."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar is a substance collected by bees along with pollen and minerals, contributing to the overall diet of the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is a sweet liquid collected by bees for food and to make honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by plants that is collected by bees for food and to make honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is the sweet liquid collected by worker bees from flowers, used for making honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey is a product derived from nectar, containing small amounts of vitamins and minerals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey is the sweet substance produced by bees from nectar and stored in the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey is the sweet substance produced by worker bees from nectar, stored in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUGAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sugar is a component that bees consume for wax secretion and the development of fat bodies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Water is a resource collected by worker bees for various purposes within the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Water is collected by bees as part of their routine, contributing to the overall diet and possibly aiding in the preservation of pollen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Water is collected by bees for various purposes within the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Water is collected by bees to dilute honey and maintain the hive's moisture levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHAPTER 3&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chapter 3 discusses when to feed the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Chapter 3 is a reference to a section discussing when to feed the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feeding is the process of providing sustenance to a bee colony, which is occasionally necessary and involves specific considerations for the type of substance used."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GRANULATED SUGAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Granulated Sugar is a form of sugar (sucrose) that is acceptable for feeding bees when pure, but impure forms can harm or kill them."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIGH-FRUCTOSE CORN SYRUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"High-Fructose Corn Syrup is another form of sugar that can be used for feeding bees, but impure forms can also harm or kill them."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MOLASSES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Molasses is an impure form of sugar that can seriously harm or kill bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANDYMAKING BY-PRODUCTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Candymaking By-Products are impure forms of sugar that can seriously harm or kill bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CORN SYRUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Corn Syrup is an impure form of sugar that can seriously harm or kill bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MAPLE SYRUP OR SAP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Maple Syrup or Sap is an impure form of sugar that can seriously harm or kill bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIGH-FRUCTOSE SYRUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"High-Fructose Syrup is an impure form of sugar, often from soft drink plants, that can seriously harm or kill bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TABLE-GRADE GRANULATED SUGAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Table-Grade Granulated Sugar is the only form of sugar that should be used for feeding bees, as it is pure and safe."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLEN SUBSTITUTE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollen Substitute is a manufactured material that can be used as a protein source for bees when pure."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen substitute is a manufactured material designed to replace natural pollen, containing components like soy flour, brewers yeast, dry skim milk, and powdered casein."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-517c563bb28c6e8e2284f65f24dada91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee Colony is the subject of feeding, requiring specific considerations for the type of substance used to ensure their health and survival."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20afd519d4aa956b66c376e48d6fc385</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLEN TRAP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
