  <data key="d2">chunk-aeb961c56fad5bba709f67c784ce1fa4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 20}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROCK 'N' ROLL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rock 'n' Roll refers to the popular music genre that began to influence Broadway productions in the late 1960s, challenging traditional musical theater styles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aeb961c56fad5bba709f67c784ce1fa4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXPERIMENTAL AND INNOVATIVE ROCK 'N' ROLL MUSIC THEATER PRODUCTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"These refer to the new style of musical theater productions that emerged in the late 1960s, blending rock 'n' roll with traditional theater elements."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aeb961c56fad5bba709f67c784ce1fa4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CULTURAL UPHEAVAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cultural Upheaval refers to the significant social and cultural changes of the late 1960s, including the influence of drugs, sex, and rock 'n' roll on society and the arts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cultural Upheaval refers to the significant social and cultural changes of the late 1960s, including the influence of drugs, sex, and rock 'n' roll on society and the arts."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aeb961c56fad5bba709f67c784ce1fa4</data>
