</node>
<node id="&quot;DRUGS, SEX, AND ROCK 'N' ROLL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drugs, Sex, and Rock 'n' Roll represents the counterculture movement of the late 1960s, which had a profound impact on the cultural and artistic landscape."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aeb961c56fad5bba709f67c784ce1fa4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ESTABLISHMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Establishment refers to the traditional and conservative values and institutions that were challenged by the cultural upheaval of the late 1960s."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aeb961c56fad5bba709f67c784ce1fa4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW COMPOSERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
