  <data key="d2">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CAREER SHIFT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Career Shift is the change in focus from a part-time job to the center of Rowley's life due to her research on translocations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BIKING TO LAB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Biking to Lab is the mode of transportation Rowley adopted to get to the lab, indicating her dedication to her research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROCKEFELLER INSTITUTE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rockefeller Institute is a scientific research institution where Peyton Rous worked and conducted his pioneering research on viruses causing cancer in chickens."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PEYTON ROUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Peyton Rous was a scientist at the Rockefeller Institute who discovered a virus capable of producing sarcomas in chickens in 1910."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SARCOMAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sarcomas are tumors that were induced in chickens by the virus discovered by Peyton Rous."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NOBEL PRIZE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Nobel Prize is an award that was eventually given to Peyton Rous for his discovery of the virus causing sarcomas in chickens, after a significant delay."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIRUS CAUSING SARCOMAS IN CHICKENS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A virus was discovered by Peyton Rous that could cause sarcomas in chickens, marking a significant breakthrough in understanding cancer origins."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cancer is a complex disease characterized by uncontrolled cell growth, which was initially thought to be unrelated to chromosomal changes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 78}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIRUS CAUSING CANCER IN HUMANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The concept of viruses causing cancer in humans was initially unclear, but the discovery of viruses causing sarcomas in chickens paved the way for further research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELECTRON MICROSCOPES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Electron microscopes allowed scientists to see viruses in greater detail, contributing to the establishment of the concept of cancer-causing viruses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUMOR-CAUSING VIRUSES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tumor-causing viruses were isolated from various animals, providing evidence for the role of viruses in cancer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1910&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DATE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1910 marks the year when Peyton Rous identified a virus capable of producing sarcomas in chickens, initiating a significant period of research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1966&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DATE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1966 marks the year when Peyton Rous was awarded the Nobel Prize, nearly five decades after his initial discovery, highlighting the long-term impact of his work."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKEPTICISM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Skepticism about the role of chromosomal changes and viruses in cancer was prevalent, reflecting the challenges in validating these concepts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELECTRON MICROSCOPY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Electron microscopy provided visual evidence of viruses, helping to establish their role in cancer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUMOR-CAUSING VIRUSES IN HUMANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The concept of tumor-causing viruses in humans was initially unclear but was supported by the discovery of similar viruses in animals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PEYTON ROUS'S DISCOVERY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Peyton Rous's discovery of the virus causing sarcomas in chickens was a pivotal moment in cancer research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROCKEFELLER INSTITUTE'S RESEARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The research conducted at the Rockefeller Institute, particularly by Peyton Rous, was instrumental in advancing our understanding of cancer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708efd6fe2a4d447a789c388f8aeed9b</data>
