</node>
<node id="&quot;THE ELVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Elves (1857) was a Broadway musical that marked the first long-run performance with fifty consecutive shows, setting a precedent for future productions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c327d240cc02f4086ef379cf45e3feef</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 15}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 70}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 111}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THE SEVEN SISTERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Seven Sisters (1860) was a highly successful musical burletta with an unprecedented 253-performance run, featuring a unique transformation scene."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c327d240cc02f4086ef379cf45e3feef</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 15}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 70}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 113}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CIVIL WAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Civil War (1861–1865) was a significant historical event that impacted theater productions, leading to a focus on Northern theaters and performances for audiences on both sides of the conflict."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c327d240cc02f4086ef379cf45e3feef</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 15}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 70}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 111}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THEATERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Theaters provided the venues for Laura Keene's productions and were central to the entertainment industry in New York City during the mid-19th century."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c327d240cc02f4086ef379cf45e3feef</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 15}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 71}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACTORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Actors were part of the performing arts community in New York City, including Laura Keene and her troupe, who performed in various productions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c327d240cc02f4086ef379cf45e3feef</data>
