  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Screened box is a container used to transport bees, typically containing workers, drones, a queen, and syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIE-OFF&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Die-off refers to the sudden death of a large number of bees, which may be considered normal but requires attention if a thick layer of dead bees begins to accumulate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCREEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Screen is part of the cage containing the bee package, through which bees extend their antennae, feet, and tongues to access the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANTENNAE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Antennae are sensory organs of the bees that help them detect and interact with their environment, extending through the screen to reach the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feet are appendages of the bees that assist in movement and cleaning, extending through the screen to reach the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TONGUES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tongues are proboscises of the bees used for feeding, extending through the screen to reach the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAINTBRUSH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Paintbrush is a tool mentioned as inappropriate for applying syrup to the screen due to the risk of brushing off bees' appendages."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cage is the container holding the bee package, with a screen allowing bees to access the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOOLS AND EQUIPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tools and equipment are necessary for setting up and maintaining the hive, including those needed for installing the bee package."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Tools and equipment include items necessary for setting up and maintaining the hive, such as a jackknife, pliers, hive tool, and protective gear."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tools and equipment refer to the necessary items for setting up and maintaining the hive, including those needed for installing the bee package."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERMANENT LOCATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Permanent location is the fixed position where the hive will be situated, requiring preparation before the installation of the bee package."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WEATHER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Weather conditions affect whether the package can be installed immediately."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEED&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feed is the act of providing syrup to the bees to ensure their survival during delays."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSTALLATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Installation is the process of putting the bees in the hive after they have been cared for."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Installation refers to the process of placing the package in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NURSE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nurse bees care for the young bees in the package, ensuring their health and development."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YOUNG BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Young bees are the ones that need to be installed in the hive to continue the colony's lifecycle."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cold is a condition to avoid when storing the package to prevent harm to the bees."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUIET PLACE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Quiet place is the environment where the package is stored before installation to minimize disturbance."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DARK PLACE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dark place is the environment where the package is stored before installation to maintain the bees' natural behavior."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COOL PLACE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cool place is the environment where the package is stored before installation to maintain optimal temperature."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JACKKNIFE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TOOL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Jackknife is a multi-purpose tool used for various tasks including puncturing the plug of sugar candy in the queen cage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jackknife is a tool used to make a small hole in the candy, facilitating the queen's exit from the cage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLIERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TOOL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pliers are used for removing the syrup can from the package."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STANDARD HIVE TOOL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TOOL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Standard hive tool is used for prying the lid from the package."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EQUIPMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Smoker is used for calming bees during installation, though it has little positive effect without honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROTECTIVE GEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EQUIPMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Protective gear includes a veil and other items that make the user comfortable while working with bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Protective gear includes items like veils worn by beekeepers to protect themselves from bee stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLUG OF SUGAR CANDY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plug of sugar candy is a substance used to protect the queen in the queen cage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTAINER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Container is a general term for the vessel used to feed the bees, often a 1-gallon glass jar."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Veil is a protective covering worn by beekeepers to shield their faces from bee stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANDY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Candy is a general term for food sources for bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Candy is used as a food source for bees, especially during confinement periods."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MARSHMALLOW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Marshmallow can be used as a substitute for queen cage candy if it is not readily available, providing a similar function in beekeeping."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marshmallow is an alternative food source for bees if the queen cage candy is unavailable."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PACKAGE OF BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Package of bees refers to a group of bees packaged for sale or transfer to a new hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NAILS OR STAPLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nails or staples are used to secure the lid of the package of bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXCITEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Excitement is a state of heightened emotion experienced by beekeepers during their first interactions with their own bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollination is the process by which bees transfer pollen from one flower to another, aiding in plant reproduction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1-GALLON GLASS JAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1-gallon glass jar is a suitable container for the feeder."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMALL SUPPORTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Small supports are tools needed for the process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STICKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sticks are tools needed for the process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sticks are used to support the inverted feeder over the hole in the inner cover, allowing bees to access the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e</data>
