<node id="&quot;QUEEN CAGE CANDY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen cage candy is a special formulation used in beekeeping to house a new queen bee, ensuring she is protected while the colony accepts her."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage candy is a specific type of candy used for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19db0c8d1d16d24d3f96396e007d18df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOUNDATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foundation is a base material used in hives to provide a surface for bees to build their comb, typically made of wax or plastic."&lt;SEP&gt;"Foundation is a sheet of wax or plastic used in beekeeping to provide a template for bees to build their comb on."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ATTENDANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Attendants are worker bees that accompany the new queen in the package, helping her integrate into the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NAIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nail is a tool used to make a small hole in the candy, facilitating the queen's exit from the cage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DISC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
