  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Worker Bee is a type of bee that performs various tasks within the hive, starting from cleaning brood cells to foraging outside."&lt;SEP&gt;"Worker Bee is a type of bee within a hive that performs various tasks such as secreting brood food and later foraging for resources."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLEANING BROOD CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cleaning Brood Cells is a task performed by Worker Bees immediately after emergence, focusing on maintaining the cleanliness of the brood cells."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ATTENDING QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Attending Queen is a task performed by Worker Bees to care for the queen bee, ensuring her well-being."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDING BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feeding Brood is a task performed by Worker Bees to nourish the developing larvae within the brood cells."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CAPPING CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Capping Cells is a task performed by Worker Bees to seal brood cells once the larvae have pupated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PACKING POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Packing Pollen is a task performed by Worker Bees to store pollen within the hive for future use."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECRETING WAX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Secreting Wax is a task performed by Worker Bees to produce wax for building honeycomb structures within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENERAL CLEANING OF HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"General Cleaning of Hive is a task performed by Worker Bees to maintain the overall cleanliness and hygiene of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RECEIVING AND PROCESSING NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Receiving and Processing Nectar is a task performed by Worker Bees to collect and process nectar for honey production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GUARDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Guarding is a task performed by Worker Bees to protect the hive from external threats."&lt;SEP&gt;"Guarding is the activity of protecting the hive from predators and ensuring the safety of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foraging is a task performed by Worker Bees to collect nectar, pollen, and water from outside the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Foraging is the activity of collecting nectar, pollen, water, and propolis outside the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMERGENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Emergence is the stage when a worker bee first emerges from its cell, marking the beginning of its life within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Muscles refer to the physical development of the worker bee, particularly those necessary for flying and performing various tasks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glands are organs within the worker bee that secrete substances necessary for various tasks such as brood food, wax, etc."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD NEST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Nest is the central area of the hive where brood cells are located and where the queen lays eggs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEART OF THE BROOD NEST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Heart of the Brood Nest refers to the central and most protected part of the brood area where the queen and her brood are primarily located."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GREAT OUTDOORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Great Outdoors refers to the external environment where worker bees go to collect nectar, pollen, and water."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HYPOPHARYNGEAL GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hypopharyngeal Glands are specialized glands in the worker bee that secrete brood food."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hypopharyngeal Glands are specialized glands in worker bees that secrete brood food for a limited period."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MANDIBULAR GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mandibular Glands are specialized glands in the worker bee that secrete substances used in nest construction and feeding."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mandibular Glands are specialized glands in worker bees that also secrete brood food for a limited period."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Food is the substance secreted by the hypopharyngeal and mandibular glands of worker bees to feed the larvae."&lt;SEP&gt;"Brood Food is the substance secreted by the hypopharyngeal glands to nourish the developing larvae."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEYCOMB STRUCTURES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honeycomb Structures are hexagonal cells built by worker bees using wax secreted from their glands."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXTERNAL THREATS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"External Threats are any dangers or challenges that the hive faces from outside sources, which worker bees must guard against."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e6f1acef4b9b291d3c2495eb33737a68</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOUSE BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"House Bee is a term used to describe a worker bee that is currently performing tasks inside the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"House Bee refers to the stage in a bee's life before becoming a field bee, where she remains in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIELD BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Field Bee is a term used to describe a worker bee that has graduated from the house bee stage and is now responsible for foraging outside the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Field Bee is the stage in a bee's life after graduating from the house bee, where she spends her days foraging for specific raw materials of colony life."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPOLIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"RESOURCE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Propolis is a resin-like substance collected by bees from tree buds, used to seal gaps in the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Propolis is a resin-like substance collected by bees from trees and used to seal gaps in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMB BUILDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Comb Building is the process of constructing hexagonal wax cells in the hive for storing honey, raising brood, and other purposes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER MONTHS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter Months refer to the colder periods of the year when certain hive activities are reduced."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD REARING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Rearing is the process of nurturing and caring for the developing larvae within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARVAE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larvae are the immature stages of bees that are cared for and fed by worker bees within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Comb is the hexagonal wax structure within the hive used for storing honey and raising brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREDATORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Predators are animals that pose a threat to the hive and its inhabitants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEVELOPING GENERATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Developing Generations refer to the new bees that are growing and maturing within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-85e24df0ba338b9be542d41e4b8587b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCOUT BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Scout Bee is a type of bee that may forage randomly, unlike other field bees who focus on specific materials."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FLOWERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Flowers are plants that bees visit for nectar and pollen, contributing to the bees' foraging activities and wing wear."&lt;SEP&gt;"Flowers are the source of nectar and pollen for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b76cb7a97a0a93c1fb8f78f65cc66f8e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOLIAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foliage is the plant material that bees come into contact with while foraging."&lt;SEP&gt;"Foliage refers to the leaves and other green parts of plants, which bees may come into contact with during foraging, causing additional wear on their wings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b76cb7a97a0a93c1fb8f78f65cc66f8e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee is a term used to describe any individual bee, including both house and field bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee refers to a social insect known for its role in pollination and honey production, often found in hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e26e1c880b5194553cd5e88d9bedc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b76cb7a97a0a93c1fb8f78f65cc66f8e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wings are the appendages of a bee used for flying, which show wear due to various activities within the hive and during foraging."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b76cb7a97a0a93c1fb8f78f65cc66f8e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BELTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Belting is a vocal technique involving a powerful, resonant sound produced in the chest register, often associated with musical theater and pop music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b76cb7a97a0a93c1fb8f78f65cc66f8e</data>
