<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;EXTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both the diaphragm and external intercostal muscles work together to increase lung capacity during inhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;INTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The diaphragm and internal intercostal muscles have opposing actions, with the diaphragm contracting during inhalation and the internal intercostal muscles contracting during exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;INHALATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The diaphragm contracts during inhalation, helping to draw air into the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;EXPIRATORY MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Expiratory muscles, including the diaphragm, work together to control respiratory pressure during exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;EXTERNAL INTERCOSTALS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both the diaphragm and external intercostals are involved in the breathing process, working together to control respiratory pressure."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;MUSCULAR ANTAGONISM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Muscular antagonism is also seen in the relationship between the diaphragm and external intercostals during respiration."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a50f580c4d4e704c505f145305237334</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;RESPIRATORY SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Diaphragm is a key muscle in the respiratory system, aiding in the process of inhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;" target="&quot;INTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The external and internal intercostal muscles have complementary roles in respiration, with the external muscles aiding inhalation and the internal muscles aiding exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;" target="&quot;INHALATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The external intercostal muscles contract during inhalation, helping to expand the thorax and increase lung volume."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INTERNAL INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;" target="&quot;EXHALATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The internal intercostal muscles contract during exhalation, helping to decrease the thorax volume and expel air from the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;THORAX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The thorax expands during inhalation due to the contraction of the diaphragm and external intercostal muscles."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;LUNGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The lungs expand during inhalation, allowing more air to enter and facilitating gas exchange."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;RESPIRATORY PRESSURE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Inhalation involves the generation of respiratory pressure."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5de4506ebf12460c924336c672dfa5b6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;THORAX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The thorax contracts during exhalation due to the relaxation of the diaphragm and the contraction of the internal intercostal muscles."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;LUNGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The lungs contract during exhalation, expelling air and facilitating gas exchange."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5d75b6e35d99dd76cf7cf11d5dd4c669</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;INTERNAL INTERCOSTALS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
