  <data key="d6">chunk-19f493d7c41902144de9bdc890a5c45a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;FUNCTIONAL PRINCIPLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Functional principles are applied to the vocal mechanism to achieve optimal performance."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19f493d7c41902144de9bdc890a5c45a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;BELT VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The belt voice technique pushes the vocal mechanism to its physiological limits."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8f0da82f9beb0da150b7eedf80de1ef0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;PHYSIOLOGICAL LIMITS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The vocal mechanism has physiological limits when performing the belt voice technique."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8f0da82f9beb0da150b7eedf80de1ef0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;RESONATORS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Resonators are part of the vocal mechanism and enhance the sound produced during belting."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8f0da82f9beb0da150b7eedf80de1ef0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;BREATH PRESSURE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Breath pressure supports the vocal mechanism during belting."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8f0da82f9beb0da150b7eedf80de1ef0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLD VIBRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vocal fold vibration is part of the vocal mechanism and is essential for producing sound during belting."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8f0da82f9beb0da150b7eedf80de1ef0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;MICROPHONE TECHNIQUES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Microphone techniques can enhance the sound produced by the vocal mechanism during belting."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8f0da82f9beb0da150b7eedf80de1ef0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;MUSIC THEATER PERFORMER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Music Theater Performers rely on the Vocal Mechanism to produce sound and must take care of it to maintain vocal health."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d0f2d558b9d85b9b6142b2eebca7786d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are managed in beekeeping to produce honey and other products."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19f493d7c41902144de9bdc890a5c45a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A beekeeper manages a colony of bees, providing care and maintaining the health of the hive."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1b0c213d997522366066834a914f43a4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;NUC&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A nucleus hive contains a colony of bees, including a queen and worker bees."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1b0c213d997522366066834a914f43a4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">41.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A package contains bees, typically a queen and worker bees, which can be used to start a new beehive."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are temporarily housed in the package during transportation or relocation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The package contains bees, which are essential for the survival and operation of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1b0c213d997522366066834a914f43a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;SMOKE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">24.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Smoke is used to calm bees, making it easier for beekeepers to handle the hive."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1b0c213d997522366066834a914f43a4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees form the core of the new colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;NEW QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The new queen becomes the leader of the bees in the package after they forget their parent queen."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are part of the parent colony before being separated for the package."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">312.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are introduced into the hive to form a new colony or join an existing one."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are managed in the hive and are the primary focus of the beekeeping process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are placed in a hive, often early in the season when there is little forage available."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees live and work within the hive, performing necessary tasks to maintain the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hive is the environment where bees live and work together."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f4b59df57b1e25c48127580d5e99112f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees collect and store pollen, adding enzymes to preserve and enhance its value, and use it as a source of vitamins, minerals, and fats."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;VITAMINS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees obtain vitamins from pollen, which is essential for the growth and development of any living organism."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;MINERALS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees collect minerals as part of nectar, pollen, and water, which are necessary for various functions at specific ages."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;FATS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees obtain fats from pollen, which are used for daily needs and stored in fat bodies within the bee's body cavity."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;FAT BODIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Fat Bodies are storage sites for food reserves within the body cavity of honey bees, primarily developed from sugar rather than pollen, and vary with the season and the age of the bee."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;WAX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Wax is secreted by bees, dependent on sugar consumption rather than pollen consumption."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees collect nectar along with pollen and minerals, contributing to their overall diet."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees produce honey from nectar, which contains small amounts of vitamins and minerals."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;SUGAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees consume sugar for wax secretion and the development of fat bodies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees collect water as part of their routine, contributing to their overall diet and possibly aiding in the preservation of pollen."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;CHAPTER 3&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chapter 3 discusses when to feed the colony, providing guidance on feeding practices."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6c6863aa983e5e43fec67000786ff8f1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;COMMUNICATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use complex communication methods to exchange information, which is crucial for their survival."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-517c563bb28c6e8e2284f65f24dada91</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey Bee is a type of bee."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2f9b065adde9eed358d0bfd3a26e87da</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;BUMBLEBEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bumblebee is a type of bee."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2f9b065adde9eed358d0bfd3a26e87da</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;ORCHID BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Orchid Bee is a type of bee."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2f9b065adde9eed358d0bfd3a26e87da</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;APOIDEA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are part of the superfamily Apoidea."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2f9b065adde9eed358d0bfd3a26e87da</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;SPECIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees refer to the family Apidae, including honey bees, bumblebees, and orchid bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2f9b065adde9eed358d0bfd3a26e87da</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;SYRUP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">34.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees feed on the syrup provided during transportation, which helps maintain their health and energy levels."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees use the syrup provided through the feeder for nourishment."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;WORKERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Workers are a part of the bee population, performing various tasks within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">65.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees must communicate with the queen after she is released from the queen cage."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees work to protect and care for the queen, ensuring her safety and the colony's survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"The queen is a part of the bee population, responsible for laying eggs and maintaining the genetic diversity of the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"The queen is the central figure in the bee colony, laying eggs and maintaining the population."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;DRONES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Drones are a part of the bee population, whose primary function is to mate with the queen."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;DEAD BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dead bees may accumulate at the bottom of the package, which is normal if the die-off is not excessive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;WOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"If the package floor is still visible, it indicates a normal die-off of bees, but a thick layer of dead bees suggests immediate installation is needed."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;INSTALLATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"If installation is delayed, the package should be installed in a hive as soon as possible to ensure the survival of the bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;SCREENED BOX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A screened box contains bees, which are transported using this container."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN CAGE CANDY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees need to consume the queen cage candy to create a path for the queen to exit the cage, facilitating her integration into the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE ENTRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use the hive entrance to enter and exit the hive, facilitating their movement and activities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-581be0c6c7e8fcfca682a8b090ad02dc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees must communicate with the queen in the queen cage before she is released, indicating a dependency on her presence."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE CONTAINER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">50.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are contained within the package container until they are released into the hive."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are temporarily housed in the package container during transportation or relocation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The package container holds the bees and is used to introduce them to the hive."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64e3fe7f9202d7b6e6d039f9e2d7aece</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees build comb and store honey on the frames within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees interact with the inner cover as part of their daily activities within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;STICKS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sticks support the inverted feeder over the hole in the inner cover, allowing bees to access the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;ATMOSPHERIC PRESSURE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Atmospheric pressure helps maintain the syrup in the feeder once an equilibrium is reached."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;SYRUP FEEDER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A leaky Syrup Feeder can cause wet bees as the syrup runs through the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7cf50994b52751855b1afce08fc2fcd5</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;" target="&quot;BOTTOM BOARD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The bottom board is placed beneath the hive body, and the outer cover is placed on top of it."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1b0c213d997522366066834a914f43a4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">19.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Outer Cover completes the installation of the Hive and is part of the Hive structure."&lt;SEP&gt;"The outer cover protects the hive from environmental factors."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7cf50994b52751855b1afce08fc2fcd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The package provides the initial bees for the new colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The beekeeper is responsible for the management and care of the new colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Brood is essential for the growth and sustainability of the new colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Frames are used to organize and support the brood and bees within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The queen is a key component of the new colony, responsible for egg-laying."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hive is the home and structure of the new colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">49.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A package can be used to start a new beehive."|&lt;SEP&gt;"A package is another method of purchasing bees, which can also be used to start a new beehive."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Package is placed in the hive during the installation process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package of bees is to be installed in the hive, replacing any deceased bees and continuing the colony's lifecycle."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"The package container is placed near the hive to facilitate the integration of bees into the existing colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b0c213d997522366066834a914f43a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edaf4a43e5efd8371106430a67f0da8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A queen cage may be used if the queen is delivered separately from the package of bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage is part of the package that contains the queen bee."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f19f304baf8025694298418378518186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;NUC&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A nuc can be used to start a new colony, similar to a package but often includes more mature bees and brood."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;SOUTHERN BEEYARD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees for the package are sourced from a southern beeyard."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-056364487121aa01a4a102f64a05ea1b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The beekeeper monitors the package and provides necessary assistance during its journey."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;BEEYARD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The package is initially made up in the beeyard, where bees are sourced from the parent colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">17.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees for the package are taken from the parent colony, which is then separated from the package."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;NEW QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The new queen is introduced into the package to replace the parent queen after the bees are separated from their parent colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;SYRUP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">50.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Package requires syrup as a feed when immediate installation cannot be performed, ensuring the survival of the bees during delays."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Syrup is added to the package to provide nutrition for the bees during their journey."&lt;SEP&gt;"The can of syrup is placed in the package to provide the bees with nutrition during transport."&lt;SEP&gt;"The package contains syrup for the bees, providing them with necessary nutrition during transport."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-309310970b70cf80a5016a8416c27ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb32ce27616da78546076c3f28b79293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccf5e4489055ac80e4d05a0eafbf7b20</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
