<edge source="&quot;NATURE&quot;" target="&quot;ROWLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Rowley's research was published in Nature in 1973, marking a significant recognition of her work."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;EVENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Translocation is the process where genetic material from chromosome 22 was moved to chromosome 9 in CML cells."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-71e5b5184b7ec9d75dd60420b76b39c0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;HUMAN POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The translocation is not a normal variation in the human population, suggesting it is specific to CML cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eacce1c9453bba22767cf5b941903415</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;NATURE JOURNAL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Nature journal initially rejected the paper on the translocation but later published it after receiving additional data."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eacce1c9453bba22767cf5b941903415</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;CHROMOSOMES OF OTHER CELLS IN THE PATIENTS' BLOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The chromosomes of other cells in the patients' blood showed forty-six normal chromosomes, contrasting with the cancer cells that had the translocation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eacce1c9453bba22767cf5b941903415</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;SPECIFIC BUT DIFFERENT CHROMOSOMAL CHANGES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Specific but different chromosomal changes are related to the translocation, indicating that similar genetic alterations can occur in different types of leukemia."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eacce1c9453bba22767cf5b941903415</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;TWO DIFFERENT TYPES OF LEUKEMIA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The translocation is found in both types of leukemia, suggesting a possible link between the chromosomal changes and the development of different types of cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eacce1c9453bba22767cf5b941903415</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;CANCERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">27.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cancers are influenced by Translocations, which Rowley suspected to be critical in the onset of cancers."&lt;SEP&gt;"The translocation is a specific chromosomal change that can cause certain types of cancer, including leukemia."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eacce1c9453bba22767cf5b941903415</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;CHROMOSOMAL CHANGES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chromosomal Changes led to Translocations, which Rowley suspected to be critical in the onset of cancers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;CANCER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Translocations are believed to cause cancer, as Rowley suspected the new juxtaposition of genes to be the critical event in the onset of cancers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;HUMAN GENOME&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Human Genome was terra incognita in the mid- to late 1970s, making the identification and understanding of translocations challenging."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;SPECIFIC GENETIC MUTATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Specific Genetic Mutations are a subset of Translocations, which Rowley observed in leukemia cases."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;DNA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"DNA is the molecule that undergoes Translocations, which are critical in the onset of cancers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;GENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Genes are segments of DNA that can be involved in Translocations, which Rowley suspected to be critical in the onset of cancers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;RESEARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Research is the process through which Translocations are discovered and studied, as done by Rowley."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cd07e490ccf823a8fb9cd8c3c52b4240</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
